{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"784cbc3b-6280-4457-a759-f86ed1d01e20","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n**In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (replaces both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`)\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <!-- Remove this -->\n  <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n\n<!-- Replace with -->\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.2\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.12.0\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**In your test code:** No changes needed — MSTest v3 still uses the same `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace, `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, and `Assert` APIs. Your `OrderServiceTests.cs` is already compatible.\n\n**Summary of key points:**\n- The `MSTest` v3 NuGet package bundles the framework + adapter + runner\n- Your `using`, attributes, and assertions remain the same\n- Consider also upgrading `TargetFramework` to `net8.0`+ if possible, though `net462` is still supported\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ba82659b-f31e-41cf-a5ee-ef5a15bf1169","outputTokens":379,"requestId":"E3CC:2B8350:AE7AEE:C72569:6A053A27"},"id":"9030274c-4a07-47d1-8a2f-1b50dbd9ea90","timestamp":"2026-05-14T02:57:52.421Z","parentId":"9e3fb06a-ad18-4593-b3fc-59bc6d4af817"}
